<subSubSection id="77D974011F47A2DED9842C3699FF1080" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="nomenclatural notes">
<paragraph id="1EE8BC9A1E0288D12301B47004EAA1F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Nomenclatural notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C6930834626826C73898A31E6E30677" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
When describing 
<taxonomicName id="173C8D04D0EA3C8144522FB9F083DA29" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ovalis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis id="571D34AD047A5E9BDB16816626E3F736" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="4EF3E9859CF4DB3A2B3AC4810B8F8377" author="Schultes, JA" journalOrPublisher="Stuttgardtiae, Sumtibus J. G. Cottae" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" refId="B94" refString="Schultes, JA, Schultes, JH, 1830. Caroli a Linné equitis Systema vegetabilium secundum classes, ordines, genera, species; cum characteribus, differentiis et synonymiis, vol. 7, part 2. Stuttgardtiae, Sumtibus J.G. Cottae" title="Caroli a Linne ́ equitis Systema vegetabilium secundum classes, ordines, genera, species; cum characteribus, differentiis et synonymiis, vol. 7, part 2." year="1830">Schultes and Schultes (1830)</bibRefCitation>
mention that their new species is based in Martius specimens from Brazil. However, the author makes no mention in which herbarium the specimens are housed or their 
<normalizedToken id="20F70D54563BA7E06432FC1697EC7929" originalValue="collectors’">collectors'</normalizedToken>
numbers. While consulting the specimens at M, we came across two 
<normalizedToken id="39B0BE4374CE85A15955BACF2064EEDC" originalValue="Martius’">Martius'</normalizedToken>
specimens (i.e. 
<emphasis id="03B7C61866D5B151F4B59CE4DEA180D0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Martius 14</emphasis>
M0242238; 
<emphasis id="C48C91360964651061FC99DAFBF3BD8A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Martius 16</emphasis>
M0242244) that matched the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="A8CB69B15C541EF250D7BE8B5F97A5ED" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ovalis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis id="06E60C223A305E493439F0BC94C11E65" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both specimens were annotated in Martius handwriting and were probably analysed by Schultes. Since the specimen 
<emphasis id="FDADB98E77174CEC811770BD55AAE531" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Martius 14</emphasis>
(M0242238) is a more complete collection, when compared with 
<emphasis id="61EEED8B0DE1C976B5A7602C63A313EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Martius 16</emphasis>
(M0242244), which is composed of two detached leaves and two inflorescences, it is selected by us as the lectotype for 
<taxonomicName id="D0D424918466297A4257566E97506BE9" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ovalis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis id="E6045DE6D5F8EEFBC32863A64689EBE4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B14A73E93366618FE972B5C322E435A0" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="taxonomical notes">
<paragraph id="30A2C1BD34AEA38A9D9B193ED60F296F" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Taxonomical notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E9B38EF22F97910B77FC267E259C9330" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName id="F24C3ACCA9620E8EB902643F4B5E37E3" class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Pontederia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pontederia ovalis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis id="75CB07F846697F4236A9723EC685BF81" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Pontederia ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been considered by most authors and online databases as either a variety (
<bibRefCitation id="45BC06B5A1943BE165EF68EC923ABDE4" author="Dubs, B" journalOrPublisher="Cladistics" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" refId="B26" refString="Dubs, B, 1998. Prodromus Florae Matogrossensis, Series B, No. 3. Betrona-Verlag." title="Prodromus Florae Matogrossensis, Series B, No. 3. Betrona-Verlag." year="1998">Dubs 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="09FA5D2DD8A97A4674BAB28A333FD8FC" author="Tropicos. org" journalOrPublisher="Mathematical Biosciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" publicationUrl="http://www.tropicos.org/" refId="B116" refString="Tropicos.org, 2018. Tropicos. Missouri Botanical Garden. http://www.tropicos.org/" title="Tropicos. Missouri Botanical Garden." url="http://www.tropicos.org/" year="2018">Tropicos.org 2018</bibRefCitation>
) or a synonym (
<bibRefCitation id="FB989579AC19B8E16F7D2E5DBBD19CCE" author="Schulz, AG" journalOrPublisher="Darwiniana" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" pagination="45 - 87" refId="B95" refString="Schulz, AG, 1942. Las Pontederiaceas de la Argentina. Darwiniana 6 (1): 45 - 87" title="Las Pontederiaceas de la Argentina." volume="6" year="1942">Schulz 1942</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A8536E035D1C530A4EF9F89ED0BF640B" author="Tropicos. org" journalOrPublisher="Mathematical Biosciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" publicationUrl="http://www.tropicos.org/" refId="B116" refString="Tropicos.org, 2018. Tropicos. Missouri Botanical Garden. http://www.tropicos.org/" title="Tropicos. Missouri Botanical Garden." url="http://www.tropicos.org/" year="2018">Tropicos.org 2018</bibRefCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName id="E2C902C7869C6CDEC107FF8BBDC108B9" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. cordata" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="cordata">
<emphasis id="508FDDC26A38309B93A8BAC9CCF4C13D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. cordata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nonetheless, both morphologically and phylogenetically, 
<taxonomicName id="E314E041CFF7E77023C039784EDB99EC" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ovalis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis id="9E40B55BD2163DF72EF98E084FFB479C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9CA1D81DB9E43D2113EABC85010F5376" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. sagittata" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="sagittata">
<emphasis id="FD9CF4109005B343A2C8F994D5CCC1D2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. sagittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, due to its pubescent inflorescence main axis and fruits with sinuate ridges. Thus, 
<taxonomicName id="825C89104884680B3855783C859BA8CE" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. ovalis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis id="093A0341CF0E558B87C86A50F61E0AB1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here re-established, being also part of the 
<taxonomicName id="497349781E74A2EB64FB6C61261DBE03" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. cordata" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="cordata">
<emphasis id="ED023BBAE880F5319382DBEC19240A1C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. cordata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex.
</paragraph>
